<node id="Protocol">
  <data key="d0">Protocol</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Protocols are raw records of meeting discussions that serve as the primary source for extracting information to create analytical notes and survey reports.&lt;SEP&gt;A protocol is a document prepared by the junior analyst following a meeting, which may include time-codes for verification before being processed by an AI agent.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a9c11e3be7004e005cff116becaaf334&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f945ba35b34fd5e6c69d4966bc1515c8</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022933</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="AI Agent">
  <data key="d0">AI Agent</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">An AI agent that processes verified protocols containing time-codes to generate analytical notes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a9c11e3be7004e005cff116becaaf334</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022934</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Junior Analyst">
  <data key="d0">Junior Analyst</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">The Junior Analyst is responsible for preparing the meeting protocol immediately after a survey or meeting concludes.&lt;SEP&gt;The Junior Analyst is a potential end-user of the system, capable of modifying documents and identifying open questions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a9c11e3be7004e005cff116becaaf334&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4c017a0092c0a18048d7d3c36d14b3bd</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022934</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="IVE">
  <data key="d0">IVE</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">IVE is an educational institution where Спикер 3 is currently studying.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a9c11e3be7004e005cff116becaaf334</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022934</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="ZOOM">
  <data key="d0">ZOOM</data>
  <data key="d1">platform</data>
  <data key="d2">Zoom is a video conferencing platform mentioned as having built-in agents capable of recording and transcribing meetings automatically.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a9c11e3be7004e005cff116becaaf334</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022934</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Telemost">
  <data key="d0">Telemost</data>
  <data key="d1">platform</data>
  <data key="d2">Telemost is the primary communication tool used by the organization for online meetings, where external cloud-based transcription services are unavailable due to security constraints.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a9c11e3be7004e005cff116becaaf334</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022934</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Chatbot">
  <data key="d0">Chatbot</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The Chatbot is designed to act as a navigator for documents and meetings, retrieving information about past discussions and details without editing the source material.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-00f42c5674c08d1c4bf50e1bd4cb1b22</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022934</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="GigaChat">
  <data key="d0">GigaChat</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">GigaChat is a specific language model mentioned as an option compliant with Russian federal laws if such compliance is required.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-00f42c5674c08d1c4bf50e1bd4cb1b22</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022935</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Yandex Models">
  <data key="d0">Yandex Models</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Models from Yandex are identified as alternatives that may be considered depending on the necessity to adhere to specific regulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-00f42c5674c08d1c4bf50e1bd4cb1b22</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022935</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Open II">
  <data key="d0">Open II</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Open source models (referred to as Open II) are suggested as viable options if legislative constraints are not a priority for the project.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-00f42c5674c08d1c4bf50e1bd4cb1b22</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022935</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Federal Laws (FZ)">
  <data key="d0">Federal Laws (FZ)</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Federal laws represent regulatory frameworks that might limit the choice of language models or require specific data handling protocols within the system.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-00f42c5674c08d1c4bf50e1bd4cb1b22</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022935</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="NDA Agreement">
  <data key="d0">NDA Agreement</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">The Non-Disclosure Agreement serves as a binding constraint preventing data transfer outside the company unless encrypted.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-00f42c5674c08d1c4bf50e1bd4cb1b22</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022935</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Project Documentation">
  <data key="d0">Project Documentation</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Project Documentation refers to materials received from the customer, including a 36-page dictionary regulation and an analytical note, used during the survey stage.&lt;SEP&gt;Project documentation is uploaded to the chatbot to establish context, with versions being fixed and used for querying rather than editing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-00f42c5674c08d1c4bf50e1bd4cb1b22&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b0c3079db7831a11a99d3914988b59cb</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022935</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Context Accumulation">
  <data key="d0">Context Accumulation</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Context accumulation refers to the process of storing and retrieving information from current or related projects to improve the chatbot's responses.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-00f42c5674c08d1c4bf50e1bd4cb1b22</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022936</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="APIs">
  <data key="d0">APIs</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">APIs are used in the initial phase to interact with various external models, allowing for flexibility before potential integration with internal systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-00f42c5674c08d1c4bf50e1bd4cb1b22</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022936</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Information Technology Department">
  <data key="d0">Information Technology Department</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Information Technology Department is responsible for potentially connecting the chatbot's API to internal company systems upon successful development.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-00f42c5674c08d1c4bf50e1bd4cb1b22</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022936</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Accuracy Requirement">
  <data key="d0">Accuracy Requirement</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The accuracy requirement specifies that the model must correctly reflect meeting discussions, including capturing missed details or correcting misinterpretations, targeting 97%+ precision.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-00f42c5674c08d1c4bf50e1bd4cb1b22</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022936</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Speaker 6">
  <data key="d0">Speaker 6</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Speaker 6 provides a brief acknowledgement ("Ugu") during the discussion but does not contribute further substantive content.&lt;SEP&gt;Speaker 6 acknowledges the proposal to continue working in the group and potentially schedule a follow-up meeting.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-00f42c5674c08d1c4bf50e1bd4cb1b22&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6018f1dfef436c4620437f8b9e42abc3</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022936</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Nikita">
  <data key="d0">Nikita</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Nikita is a speaker who interrupts to clarify whether the Analytical Note and Survey Report are identical documents or distinct ones.&lt;SEP&gt;Nikita is a participant in the discussion who asks for permission to interrupt and clarifies the distinction between documents.&lt;SEP&gt;Nikita is a project participant who provided insights on the importance of clear terminology and emphasized that developers rarely participate in the survey phase except for expert opinions.&lt;SEP&gt;Nikita is a participant whose name is called out by Speaker 1 during the discussion.&lt;SEP&gt;Nikita is an individual whose approval or availability is required to schedule another meeting before the end of the week.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e4b2511c293a18a34a2f9ee769dfe73&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b81f88fd1f77db0dbb394dd66a377029&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f945ba35b34fd5e6c69d4966bc1515c8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6018f1dfef436c4620437f8b9e42abc3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b0c3079db7831a11a99d3914988b59cb</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022936</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Functional Customer">
  <data key="d0">Functional Customer</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Functional Customer is defined as the role responsible for defining business requirements, such as processes for coal or oil processing, distinct from IT specialists.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e4b2511c293a18a34a2f9ee769dfe73</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022937</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="IT Department">
  <data key="d0">IT Department</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The IT Department refers to a company's internal service responsible for technical support, software installation, and infrastructure maintenance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e4b2511c293a18a34a2f9ee769dfe73</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022937</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="1C RP">
  <data key="d0">1C RP</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">1C RP is described as a large-scale enterprise product implemented by companies that may exceed the capabilities of their internal IT staff.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e4b2511c293a18a34a2f9ee769dfe73</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022937</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Center For Automation And Support">
  <data key="d0">Center For Automation And Support</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Center For Automation And Support is an organization with approximately 200 employees, including 50-60 analysts who handle high loads.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e4b2511c293a18a34a2f9ee769dfe73</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022937</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Document Review Process">
  <data key="d0">Document Review Process</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Document Review Process involves analyzing a document's structure and content to identify misinterpretations or incorrect terms, calculated by the ratio of correct pages to total pages.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e4b2511c293a18a34a2f9ee769dfe73</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022937</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Scalability">
  <data key="d0">Scalability</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Scalability refers to the system's ability to handle increased load, potentially through monolithic expansion or horizontal scaling with containerization support.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e4b2511c293a18a34a2f9ee769dfe73</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022937</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Video Recording">
  <data key="d0">Video Recording</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">A video recording of the meeting is a potential resource requested by participants for verifying transcription accuracy during development.&lt;SEP&gt;The Video Recording refers to the captured footage of the meeting, sought by developers for testing transcription accuracy and system validation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e4b2511c293a18a34a2f9ee769dfe73&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6018f1dfef436c4620437f8b9e42abc3</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022938</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="System Analyst">
  <data key="d0">System Analyst</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">The System Analyst (Junior or Senior) is the specialist responsible for creating PPM schemes and refining details in analytical notes.&lt;SEP&gt;A junior or senior system analyst who works with the tool and may also serve as a functional customer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e4b2511c293a18a34a2f9ee769dfe73&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f945ba35b34fd5e6c69d4966bc1515c8</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022938</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Accountant">
  <data key="d0">Accountant</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">An accountant identified as an example of a user who would work within the 1C RP product rather than the IT department.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e4b2511c293a18a34a2f9ee769dfe73</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022938</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Director">
  <data key="d0">Director</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">A director mentioned as another potential user who might access the 1C RP system for management purposes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e4b2511c293a18a34a2f9ee769dfe73</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022938</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Bakery Owner">
  <data key="d0">Bakery Owner</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">An example of a business owner (e.g., of a bakery) who understands product details like pirog pricing but lacks IT knowledge.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e4b2511c293a18a34a2f9ee769dfe73</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022938</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Pirog">
  <data key="d0">Pirog</data>
  <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
  <data key="d2">A type of food item used as an example for inventory tracking and cost calculation in non-IT projects.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e4b2511c293a18a34a2f9ee769dfe73</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022938</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Customer">
  <data key="d0">Customer</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">The Customer is a stakeholder who agrees on responsibilities and answers; their feedback is crucial for correcting misunderstandings and ensuring protocols match actual discussions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b81f88fd1f77db0dbb394dd66a377029&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f945ba35b34fd5e6c69d4966bc1515c8</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022939</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Project Team Members">
  <data key="d0">Project Team Members</data>
  <data key="d1">group</data>
  <data key="d2">Members of the project team may inadvertently record assumptions made before or after meetings as facts within the protocol, leading to inaccuracies if not verified with the customer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b81f88fd1f77db0dbb394dd66a377029</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022939</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Meeting Protocol">
  <data key="d0">Meeting Protocol</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">The Meeting Protocol is a document intended to accurately capture discussion details, responsibilities, and agreements; it often suffers from delays in preparation due to analyst workload and context switching.&lt;SEP&gt;A document recording meeting details, including mandatory fields like date, agenda, participants, and optional sections like open questions or stamps.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b81f88fd1f77db0dbb394dd66a377029&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4c017a0092c0a18048d7d3c36d14b3bd</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022939</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Analytical Note">
  <data key="d0">Analytical Note</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">The Analytical Note is a summary document combining information from all meeting protocols, typically ranging up to 50 pages, prepared at the end of the survey phase.&lt;SEP&gt;An analytical note is typically a structured document with a volume of up to 50 pages, containing processed information from protocols including functional requirements and process models.&lt;SEP&gt;The Analytical Note is a document prepared by analysts based on project documentation to define requirements and scope.&lt;SEP&gt;A document prepared after all meeting protocols are finalized and approved by the client, based on the collected documentation.&lt;SEP&gt;A generated document that can be refined by analysts and used to retrain the underlying model based on new data.&lt;SEP&gt;The Analytical Note is a final document that requires at least one protocol as a mandatory field for generation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b81f88fd1f77db0dbb394dd66a377029&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f945ba35b34fd5e6c69d4966bc1515c8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-98ed998bba253bb64419418a25b74c96&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4c017a0092c0a18048d7d3c36d14b3bd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6018f1dfef436c4620437f8b9e42abc3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b0c3079db7831a11a99d3914988b59cb</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022939</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Survey Report">
  <data key="d0">Survey Report</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">The Survey Report is a comprehensive document exceeding 50 pages in length, distinct from the Analytical Note but serving a similar purpose of summarizing the survey results.&lt;SEP&gt;A survey report is a larger document ranging from 50 to over 200 pages, often detailing extensive findings and current state descriptions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b81f88fd1f77db0dbb394dd66a377029&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f945ba35b34fd5e6c69d4966bc1515c8</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022939</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="1C Object Terminology">
  <data key="d0">1C Object Terminology</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">1C Object Terminology refers to specific professional terms used by analysts (e.g., 'nomenclature catalog') instead of simple language when documenting product details like goods and services.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b81f88fd1f77db0dbb394dd66a377029</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022939</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Meeting Recording Assistant">
  <data key="d0">Meeting Recording Assistant</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">The Meeting Recording Assistant is a proposed AI tool designed to process meeting recordings or transcripts to generate draft protocols, saving time for analysts by highlighting unclear sections.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b81f88fd1f77db0dbb394dd66a377029</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022940</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Forest">
  <data key="d0">Forest</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Forest is an internal company where the speakers work and which has conducted internal projects involving automation and analytical note creation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b81f88fd1f77db0dbb394dd66a377029</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022940</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="47-Page Document">
  <data key="d0">47-Page Document</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">A specific example of an internal analytical note mentioned by the speaker, consisting of 47 pages, which is currently being edited before it can be shared.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b81f88fd1f77db0dbb394dd66a377029</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022940</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Functional Requirements Registry">
  <data key="d0">Functional Requirements Registry</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">A registry listing functional requirements, categorized by classes such as data migration or integrations, with links to specific protocols where they were discussed.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f945ba35b34fd5e6c69d4966bc1515c8</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022940</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Business Process Description">
  <data key="d0">Business Process Description</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">A section in the analytical note describing current business processes, often presented in table format or indicated for PPM scheme creation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f945ba35b34fd5e6c69d4966bc1515c8</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022940</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="MTR File">
  <data key="d0">MTR File</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">An external document used as a source of information regarding current data views and naming conventions within the project context.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f945ba35b34fd5e6c69d4966bc1515c8</data>
  <data key="d4">MeetTest.docx</data>
  <data key="d5">1777022941</data>
